---
name: coroutine-basic
description: Coroutine primitive — create, resume, suspend, Yielded/Returned
backends: [int, js, v2]
---

# Coroutine — single yield then return

```scalascript
val co = coroutineCreate[Int, Unit, String] { () =>
  suspend(1)
  suspend(2)
  suspend(3)
  "done"
}
println(coroutineResume(co, ()))
println(coroutineResume(co, ()))
println(coroutineResume(co, ()))
println(coroutineResume(co, ()))
```

# Coroutine — two-way value passing

```scalascript
val pingpong = coroutineCreate[String, String, String] { () =>
  val b = suspend("ping")
  val c = suspend(b + "-pong")
  c + "-final"
}
println(coroutineResume(pingpong, ""))
println(coroutineResume(pingpong, "A"))
println(coroutineResume(pingpong, "B"))
```

# Coroutine — while loop

```scalascript
val counter = coroutineCreate[Int, Unit, Unit] { () =>
  var n = 0
  while n < 3 do
    suspend(n)
    n = n + 1
}
println(coroutineResume(counter, ()))
println(coroutineResume(counter, ()))
println(coroutineResume(counter, ()))
println(coroutineResume(counter, ()))
```
